}

Review: Traces show a pronounced tail-latency (duration_p95) spike at ~2024-01-19 17:14:00 UTC on the recommendationservice↔productcatalogservice path (severity ≈1.89×P95). Productcatalogservice metrics at the same time show elevated workload and CPU (workload and cpu first ≥ P95 at 2024-01-19 17:14:00 UTC; severity ratios ~1.006 and ~1.026). Logs show no error_count increases. By the localization rules (most-downstream faulty service in a trace chain and corroborating resource pressure), productcatalogservice is the root cause and the likely failure reason is high CPU usage due to a workload surge.

